2.10. 	We recommended and the management assured to comply the following:
a. 	Require the Municipal Assessor to expedite the processing of land titles in the name of the Municipality of Sapad to prevent potential adverse claims and legal disputes;
b. 	Mandate the Municipal Accountant to secure copies of titles and donation documents for reconciliation with accounting records, ensuring accuracy and compliance with financial reporting standards and to submit the complete Notes to Financial Statements to provide transparency and a clear breakdown of reported balances;
c. 	Instruct the Budget Officer to allocate sufficient funding for the titling and legal processing of these lands, ensuring that financial constraints do not hinder the regularization process;
d. 	Require the GSO to maintain and document all Deeds of Sale, Deeds of Donation, and other land transactions, ensuring traceability of land ownership; and
e. Direct the Municipal Legal Officer to actively assist in resolving legal obstacles affecting the titling of lands, particularly in addressing estate tax concerns, facilitating the issuance of patents, and ensuring legal compliance in land acquisitions. The Legal Officer should provide clear legal guidance and support to the Municipal Assessor to expedite the regularization of untitled lands and protect municipality assets from future claims or encroachments.

