To require the Municipal Treasurer to maintain the cashbooks accordingly by adopting the following measures:

1.  Update the cashbook by fund daily based on the Report of Collection and Deposits submitted by collecting clerks;

2.   Closely monitor and ensure the accuracy and physical existence of cash on hand by reconciling the daily cash on hand with the cashbook balance;

3.  Reconcile the cashbook balance with the accounting records every end of the month and take up immediately necessary corrections in books requiring adjustments to reconcile both the cashbook and the general ledger;

4.  Close the cashbooks at the end of each month by double –ruling below the last entries in the cashbook;

5.  Issue a certification as to the correctness and completeness of the recorded transactions at month-end after the last entry in the cashbook.

